# Frontend Architecture Rules

## 1. Architectural Style
Frontend must follow a feature-based, component-driven architecture.

---

## 2. Core Structure

### Components
- UI must be composed of reusable components
- Components must be small, focused, and single-purpose
- Avoid large “god components”

### Pages
- Pages represent route-level UI composition
- Pages must assemble components, not contain business logic

### Services
- All external communication (API calls) must be handled in services
- Components must never call APIs directly

### State Management
- State must be managed using a consistent strategy (store or hooks-based)
- Business state must be separated from UI state where possible

---

## 3. Data Flow Rule
Data flow must be unidirectional:
API → Service → State → Component → UI

---

## 4. Separation of Concerns
- UI rendering logic must stay in components
- Data fetching must stay in services
- State orchestration must be separated from presentation logic

---

## 5. Dependency Rule
- Components must depend on services, not direct API clients
- Services may depend on external APIs or adapters